children.subject: I'm also a Stats major as well and need 133 and to take it much sooner rather than later

Check out https://eecs.berkeley.edu/resources/undergrads/eecs/degree-reqs/enrollment-policy

TLDR: 

"A small number of seats will be held for EECS and declared-CS juniors and seniors, and other College of Engineering majors (outside of EECS) until Phase II ends."

"EE 16A is a heavily impacted course.  Students who fall into categories 2-5 may wish to use Phase I units to enroll in this course."

So both classes are phase I material... which means you're best sticking with whatever you're already enrolled in. Phase 2 is just around the corner though, and some of the lab section waitlists for stat 133 aren't that bad. Best of luck!

I'd stick to EE16A. You need it to graduate, whereas stat 133 might be cool but you can always take another elective class in case things don't go your way. And you also have less priority over freshmen and sophomores for EE16A as a junior with the new policy changes iirc. Posting this as a followup since I'm just a student and my information might not be entirely correct, but phase II is a coming and I hope this helps.

history.content: I'm a junior CS major and I am enrolled in 16A for next semester, but also really want to get into Stat133 which is becoming very full. So my question is should I risk dropping 16A, signing up for 133, and hope I can get into 16A phase two since it got expanded? Any insight or advice would be appreciated thanks!
